title: 2020 New York State Senate election
added: In the 2018 election the Democratic Party won a majority of seat with 39 of the 63 seats in the New York State Senate, gaining 8 seats from the Republicans. The Republican Party won 23 seats becoming the minority in the State Senate for the first time since 2010. [[Simcha Felder]] was the only Democratic who continued to caucus with the Republicans.
